==English==
===Alternative spellings===
Also [[chatteratis]] with a plural -s as if from a singular ''*chatterati''.

===Etymology===
Blend of [[chatter]] and [[litterati]] and [[glitterati]] coined by Peter Simmons in 1998 and used frequently in letters to newspapers and online journals, since used by a number of people in published works.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''chatterati''' ''plural'' 

# People who are renowned to [[chat]], [[argue]] and [[debate]] excessively

===Synonyms===
* [[chattering classes]]

